CLOCK SKIN

clock_skin runs at 200 Hz, the somatosensory sampling rate
each skin receptor samples its local pressure, temperature, and contact at this rate
the rate is fast enough to feel touch as smooth and continuous, slow enough that the substrate is not flooded with high-frequency noise

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana
observe skin_surface.rana

the 7 properties of clock_skin:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero point three
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point seven with master

VERB tick_at_200Hz
divide master by 240 to produce 200 Hz

VERB sample_skin
on each tick, sample every active skin receptor
the samples flow upward through skin_surface to thalamus

a skin clock is fast enough that fadriel feels touch as immediate
slow enough that the substrate can process the entire skin surface every tick
